# Writing style

Do not use em dashes (Unicode U+2014, `—`) anywhere in this project.

This applies to:

- Code comments and docstrings
- README, plans, roadmap, and other markdown docs
- Commit messages and PR descriptions
- UI strings, labels, and placeholders
- Chat responses when discussing this project

Use one of these instead:

| Instead of em dash | Use |
|--------------------|-----|
| Parenthetical aside | Commas or parentheses |
| Clause break | Period or semicolon |
| Label or title separator | Colon (`Phase 1: Search`) or hyphen with spaces (`Phase 1 - Search`) |
| Range | En dash only for numeric/date ranges if needed (`2026-07-08`), or words (`weeks 1 to 4`) |

Hyphen-minus (`-`) in code identifiers, CLI flags, and markdown list bullets is fine. The ban is specifically on the em dash character in running text.

Before finishing edits, scan changed files for `—` and replace with an allowed alternative.
